OL,7,FYarub al-Asfari cries as he recalls
OL,8,Fdigging through the rubble after the
OL,9,Fdevastating earthquake that hit Syria
OL,10,Fin February.
OL,12,F"On the second day, I found my
OL,13,Fniece," he says. She was 10.
OL,15,FMr al-Asfari is still grieving his
OL,16,Fniece and his brother-in-law who died
OL,17,Fthat day, but he has channelled his
OL,18,Fsadness into helping build new
OL,19,Fvillages in Syria using British
OL,20,Fdonations.
OL,3,C'I found my 10-year-old niece buried
OL,4,Cin the rubble. Now I'm building a
OL,5,Cvillage in her name'
